      <item>
        <title>Call It Like It Is</title>
        <author>hello@minutestomidnight.co.uk (Simone Silvestroni)</author>
        <description><![CDATA[
          I read with interest recent posts by <a href='https://www.thisdaysportion.com/posts/say-what-you-mean-and-be-damned/'>Leon</a> and <a href='https://bix.blog/posts/2025-10-13-kicking-puppies-is-beside-the-point/'>Bix</a> about&nbsp;—&nbsp;in essence&nbsp;—&nbsp;how to deal with taking a stance, by calling things out with their names.
          <p>At the same time, I’ve exchanged very interesting private conversations about the very same topic, in particular with a friend, a former (and future, hopefully) music collaborator from Italy. It surprised me how all this happened simultaneously despite the people involved being completely unrelated to each other.</p>

<p>I won’t get into the nitty-gritty of Leon’s and Bix’s points of view, as they have done it extensively on their websites, while I’d love to touch on where my other line of conversation landed. We both called a spade a spade, didn’t mince words, and agreed on how we’re handling these tiring times: by taking a solid stance.</p>

<p>Our position is pretty clear: as we’re living through what I can only describe as pre-fascism (the totalitarian type), akin to the 1920s in Italy and the 1930s in Germany, we found common ground into calling out what’s going on in the most direct way.</p>

<p>Taking a stance involves decisions. Things like quitting online services, or stop giving money to bootlickers sycophants like Apple and others, using the word <em>fascist</em> towards anyone showing support to the current authoritarian techno-supported wave. Things like cutting off people as well, why not.</p>

<p>My grandfather lived through similar times, joined an antifascist party, took a stance debating his Mussolini-adoring father-in-law, and what did he get in return? <a href="https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/after-1989-full-story/">Sent to Sachsenhausen for four years</a>. So yes, I stand firm against anyone who supports fascism in all its modern incarnations, even indirectly.</p>

          <hr /><p><a href="mailto:hello@minutestomidnight.co.uk?subject=Call%20It%20Like%20It%20Is">Reply via email</a></p>]]>
        </description>
        <pubDate>Sun, 19 Oct 2025 11:35:58 +0100</pubDate>
        <link>https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/calling-it-like-it-is/</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="false">https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/calling-it-like-it-is/</guid>
