      <item>
        <title>Getting Ready for the Winter. Part 2, Writing Music</title>
        <author>hello@minutestomidnight.co.uk (Simone Silvestroni)</author>
        <description><![CDATA[
          After resuming my bullet journal a couple weeks ago, I started planning my next creative music endeavours. This time, back to writing and producing my own messages.
          <p>What’s taking shape, out of my scribbled notes on paper, are two distinct concept albums. Probably shorter than the previous one. I’m seeing 6-song works for now. I have names of all the collaborators I want to work with, a rough flexible timeline, and the themes.</p>

<p>Although, once that was lined up in black and white, it occurred to me how a few ideas have been living in my head rent free for the last six months or so: producing and releasing singles, which is something I’ve never done and never thought about.</p>

<p>As a first approach to returning to my music, I’ll be working on 4 singles, to be released in the Winter, hopefully, to be followed by my second concept album, still known by its working title <strong>Less Than One</strong>, and a third thematic work after that. The latter is still untitled, but I know it will be in Italian.</p>

<h2 id="the-singles">The Singles</h2>

<p>The first two are re-editions of a couple songs from <a href="https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/after-1989/">After 1989</a>: <em>Skinny Kid</em> and <em>The Day Before</em>.</p>

<p><em>Skinny Kid</em> will be partly re-recorded and fully remixed, with both title and lyrics in German. It’s a pet project conceived with <a href="https://bearte.space/">Bea Henkel</a>, with whom I share part of the song’s inspiration — Bea’s grandmother, <a href="https://bearte.space/liddieslied/">Liddi Jenni Möller</a>, was murdered by the Nazi, at the age of 33.</p>

<p><em>The Day Before</em> is my favourite song from the album, but suffered from bad production choices I made back then, which I’ve always wanted to rectify. I’ll wipe and remake a few parts, keeping what I’ve always liked, and remixing to my taste.</p>

<p>The other two singles will be unreleased originals. The first one, <em>Rainy Days Ahead</em>, is co-written with long-time collaborator and friend Gerald Duchene. It’s about the weird unsettling fascination I hold towards a door I see every day when I go to work. Leading to offices and labs, now part of the department of Psychology of the University of Cambridge, it’s where Robert Oppenheimer studied in the 1920s. It became sadly known in recent years as the place where the core idea of what became the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook%E2%80%93Cambridge_Analytica_data_scandal">Cambridge Analytica scandal</a> came out.</p>

<p>Lastly, but this I’m not entirely sure about yet, a fourth single could come out of a discarded song from <em>After 1989</em>. Its working title was <em>Come To This Gate</em>, and featured a lovely guitar arpeggio with a counterpoint of mellow piano melody. In 2019 it didn’t make the cut, but I’ve always liked it.</p>

<h2 id="the-concept-albums">The Concept Albums</h2>

<p><em>Less Than One</em> is all about the mechanisms used by fascism to insinuate into people’s mind, and the insufferable way these things have a tendency to repeat across time. I come from a country that holds the sad record of having invented fascism, having also decided to send their grandchildren back to power by democratic means on its 100th anniversary three years ago.</p>

<p>The as-of-yet untitled second concept album, in Italian, will likely be mostly spoken-word alternated with proper sung choruses. It’s the culmination of a 35-years personal obsession with the story of Post-War Italy, with its problematic geopolitical crucial position in the “iron curtain”.</p>

          <hr /><p><a href="mailto:hello@minutestomidnight.co.uk?subject=Getting%20Ready%20for%20the%20Winter.%20Part%202,%20Writing%20Music">Reply via email</a></p>]]>
        </description>
        <pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 15:40:35 +0100</pubDate>
        <link>https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/getting-ready-for-the-winter-part-2/</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="false">https://minutestomidnight.co.uk/getting-ready-for-the-winter-part-2/</guid>
